Multi-Agent Research Assistant

An autonomous AI research pipeline that searches the web, scrapes pages,
stores findings in a vector database, and writes a structured research
report from a single topic input. Built entirely with free tools.


WHAT IT DOES

Type any research topic and the system automatically:
- Searches the web using DuckDuckGo
- Scrapes and summarizes the top 3 result pages
- Stores all findings in a ChromaDB vector database
- Retrieves the most relevant chunks semantically
- Writes a full structured research report using LLaMA 3


ARCHITECTURE

User Input
    ↓
Search Agent    →  DuckDuckGo search  →  LLaMA 3 summarization
    ↓
Scraper Agent   →  Visit top 3 URLs  →  BeautifulSoup  →  summarization
    ↓
ChromaDB Store  →  HuggingFace embeddings  →  vector storage
    ↓
Writer Agent    →  Retrieve top 5 chunks  →  LLaMA 3 70B  →  report
    ↓
Streamlit UI    →  Render report


TECH STACK

LangGraph      - Multi-agent orchestration with stateful graph
LangChain      - Agent and tool abstractions
Groq API       - Free LLaMA 3.3 70B inference
ChromaDB       - Local vector store for semantic memory
HuggingFace    - all-MiniLM-L6-v2 embeddings, free and local
DuckDuckGo     - Free web search, no API key needed
BeautifulSoup4 - Web scraping and HTML parsing
Streamlit      - Interactive web UI
Python Dotenv  - Environment variable management


SETUP AND INSTALLATION

Prerequisites
- Python 3.10 or above
- Free Groq API key from https://console.groq.com

Step 1 - Clone the repository
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/research-assistant.git
    cd research-assistant

Step 2 - Create virtual environment
    Windows:
        python -m venv venv
        venv\Scripts\activate
    Mac and Linux:
        python -m venv venv
        source venv/bin/activate

Step 3 - Install dependencies
    pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 4 - Add your Groq API key
    Create a .env file in the root folder and add:
    GROQ_API_KEY=groq_api_key

Step 5 - Run the app
    streamlit run main.py
    Open your browser at http://localhost:8501


CONFIGURATION

All settings are centralized in config.py. Change any value once
and it updates across the entire project automatically.

    SEARCH_MODEL = "llama-3.3-70b-versatile"
    WRITER_MODEL = "llama-3.3-70b-versatile"
    MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS = 3
    CHROMA_DIR = "./chroma_db"
    EMBEDDING_MODEL = "sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2"
    DEVICE = "cpu"
    LOG_LEVEL = "INFO"


LOGGING

Every agent logs its activity with timestamps to the terminal so you
can see exactly which step is running and how long it takes.

    search_agent  - INFO - Searching for: Quantum computing
    search_agent  - INFO - Search complete
    scraper_agent - INFO - Scraping: https://example.com
    scraper_agent - WARNING - Empty content from https://blocked.com
    vector_store  - INFO - Stored 2 docs in ChromaDB
    writer_agent  - INFO - Writing final report
    writer_agent  - INFO - Report complete


REPORT STRUCTURE

Every generated report follows this structure:

    1. Executive Summary
    2. Background and Context
    3. Key Findings
    4. Analysis and Insights
    5. Conclusions and Recommendations


ERRORS FIXED DURING DEVELOPMENT

These are real production errors encountered and resolved:

    ModuleNotFoundError langchain.schema
    Cause - LangChain moved modules in newer versions
    Fix   - Changed to langchain_core.messages

    ImportError AgentExecutor
    Cause - AgentExecutor deprecated in new LangChain
    Fix   - Rewrote search agent as a plain function

    groq.BadRequestError model decommissioned
    Cause - Groq retired llama3-8b-8192
    Fix   - Updated to llama-3.3-70b-versatile

    ValueError Expected Embeddings non-empty
    Cause - Empty scraped pages sent to ChromaDB
    Fix   - Added content filter before storing

    StreamlitDuplicateElementId
    Cause - Old code still present in main.py
    Fix   - Cleared file and added unique key


KEY CONCEPTS

LangGraph StateGraph
Every agent shares a ResearchState dictionary. Each agent reads from
it and writes back to it as it completes its job.

RAG - Retrieval Augmented Generation
Scraped content is embedded and stored in ChromaDB. The writer agent
retrieves the most relevant chunks before writing the report.

Multi-Agent Pipeline
Instead of one LLM doing everything, specialized agents collaborate
with each doing one job they are best at.

Centralized Config
All model names and settings live in config.py. When Groq
decommissioned llama3-8b-8192, only one line needed changing.

Production Logging
Every agent logs what it is doing with timestamps so you can trace
exactly which step is slow or failing.


